        <div class="about--right about--text about--text--h2 mb-45">
          <p>I've always liked telling stories. Even in my career as a software developer, I realized that my passion was to teach and inform. This started a long road to
become a filmmaker.</p>
          <p>When I was eighteen, I saw the first documentary that really affected me: <a href="https://letterboxd.com/film/streetwise/">Streetwise</a>:</p>
          <p class="text-center"><img class=" max-h-48" src="https://a.ltrbxd.com/resized/film-poster/2/2/9/6/8/22968-streetwise-0-230-0-345-crop.jpg?k=8614ce1ec7" alt="Streetwise"/></p>
          <p>I sat there watching this film about homeless kids in Seattle and something amazing happened. I got engaged with the story of real people first the first time. It was the first time I realized how important storytelling was to me.
Making documentaries has been a special gift. It has allow me to ask difficult questions of myself while exploring the lives of the people around me. I love it.</p>

